This paper discusses a privacy system that leverages differential privacy to protect LinkedIn members' data while providing audience engagement insights for marketing analytics. The paper focuses on the technical details of the differentially private algorithms and privacy safeguards used to provide results that can be used with existing real-time data analytics platforms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.CR (cryptography and security), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.SI (social and information networks), and cs.IR (information retrieval).
